# camera-raspberrypi

Some simple test code snippets related to the raspberry
pi camera. Note: some if not all of the content was stolen 
from the internet, various sources.


* install the camer following the instructions provided.
* enable the camera:
    - sudo raspi-config

* test the camera:
    - raspistill -o image.jpg

* Install some python libraries (may already be there):
    - sudo apt-get install python-picamera python3-picamera

* Some python coding:
    + timedsnap.py  timedvideo.py

* In order to view the movies you created:
    - cd Desktop
    - omxplayer video.h264
